title: Harvard-trained psychologist: If you use any of these 8 toxic phrases, ‘your relationship is in trouble’
description: Harvard psychologist and "Letting Go of Your Ex" author Dr. Cortney Warren reveals the toxic phrases that can destroy a relationship, and what to say instead.

title: Shares of Palantir pop as it reports first profitable quarter
description: Palantir's revenue for the quarter increased 18% year over year, and its U.S. commercial revenue grew 12%.

title: White House defends shooting down three aerial objects, despite not knowing who launched them or why
description: The White House on Monday said it doesn't yet know what the aerial objects they shot down this weekend are, who owns them or what they were doing.

title: Lidar makers Ouster and Velodyne complete their merger, creating a sector powerhouse
description: The merger creates a lidar powerhouse with more than 850 customers and about $315 million in cash on hand.

title: Inflation report due Tuesday has the potential to deliver some bad news
description: All market eyes Tuesday will be on the release of the Labor Department's consumer price index.

title: Ford to move forward with $3.5 billion EV battery plant with Chinese partner
description: Ford will own the new facility through a wholly owned subsidiary instead of operating it as a joint venture, which Ford has done with non-China partners.

title: Meta's chief business officer will leave the company after 13 years
description: Meta's Chief Business Officer Marne Levine is stepping down after 13 years with the company, Meta announced in a release Monday.

title: Europe is looking to tackle sky-high debt loads after signs it will dodge a recession
description: European officials sighed with relief Monday after new data suggested the region will avoid an economic recession.

title: There’s a new inflation warning for consumers coming from the supply chain
description: Inflation has dropped rapidly helping the Fed and economy, but there’s a sticky source in the supply chain related to inventory gluts and weak consumer demand.

title: Ukraine plots post-war rebuilding effort with JPMorgan Chase as economic advisor
description: One year into its conflict with Russia, which invaded Ukraine in February 2022, Ukraine's government is laying the groundwork to help rebuild the country.

title: Turkey-Syria reconstruction costs to come to 'billions of dollars,' World Bank says
description: The World Bank has slated roughly $1.8 billion of funding to Turkey and is pursuing relief aid for Syria, following last week's devastating earthquakes.

title: Chinese e-commerce giant Pinduoduo splashes on Super Bowl ad for its Temu U.S. shopping site
description: It is rare for a Chinese firm to buy a Super Bowl ad spot, which cost millions of dollars.

title: British semiconductor bosses threaten to move overseas as U.S. and EU splurge on chips
description: U.K. semiconductor bosses are pleading with the government for subsidies amid fears that some chip firms will be forced to move overseas.

title: A big bang or a grinding assault? What to expect from Russia's new offensive in Ukraine
description: The scope of Russia's offensive remains uncertain but whatever happens, it comes at a tricky time for Kyiv.

title: Analysts see short-term strength, long-term 'generational shift' in copper prices
description: Along with experiencing a short-term supply shortage, copper is set to undergo a "generational shift" in demand as decarbonization ramps up, according to BNY Mellon.

title: India's largest insurer LIC says it may review stake in Adani after management meeting
description: India's largest insurer LIC said it 'might' review its stake in Adani Group after meeting with the management.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Oil popped and stocks slumped — it feels like 2022 again for markets
description: As oil popped and stocks slumped, it feels like markets are reliving the bad days of 2022. But investors still hope for a fresh start to the year.

title: Chinese EV brand Zeekr is now worth more than Xpeng
description: Geely-backed electric car brand Zeekr said Monday it's now valued at $13 billion after a $750 million raise from Chinese battery giant CATL and others.

title: Moody's cuts outlook for four Adani group companies, cites rapid declines in market value
description: Moody's lowered its outlook for four Adani Group companies, citing a "significant and rapid decline" in the market values of the entities.

title: Singapore's budget expected to focus on inflation and support for laid off workers
description: Rising inflation and layoffs are among the concerns of Singaporeans and are expected to be addressed in the Singapore Budget 2023 on Feb. 14.
